<body class="font-sans antialiased text-premium-dark">

<!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Premium Neutrals (Stone Backgrounds, Amber/Gold Accents, Charcoal Text) -->
<!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is structured logically for a blogger researching a card comparison article. 
     1. Strategic Foundation: Establishes the core narrative (Anti-miles, pro-hotel VIP).
     2. Interactive Spend Simulator: Allows the user to verify the ROI of the Hilton card dynamically at different spend levels, proving the "2M JPY" sweet spot.
     3. Competitor Analysis: Uses interactive tabs and a dual-axis chart to compare against Marriott and other premium cards, focusing on the lounge access barrier.
     4. Blog Architecture: An interactive accordion outlining the final blog post structure, synthesizing the data into an actionable writing guide. 
     This structure takes the user from raw strategy to data proof, to competitive context, and finally to content creation. -->
<!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
     - Spend vs ROI -> Goal: Change/Simulate -> Viz: Range Slider + Dynamic Text -> Justification: Clearly demonstrates the threshold logic (Diamond status at 2M JPY).
     - Competitor Details -> Goal: Organize -> Viz: Interactive Tabs -> Justification: Keeps the UI clean while allowing deep dives into specific competitors without scrolling.
     - Annual Fee vs Lounge Hurdle -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Chart.js Bar/Line Combo Chart -> Justification: Visually exposes the massive gap between Hilton (2M) and Marriott (4M) for lounge access. 
     - Libraries: Chart.js used for the chart. Vanilla JS for tabs and sliders.
     - NO SVG or Mermaid used. Unicode characters act as iconography. -->
<!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

<nav class="bg-premium-surface border-b border-premium-border sticky top-0 z-50 shadow-sm">
